-- Gazprom Neft Boosts Oil Refining By 7.3% in 2007
-- Greg Walters
-- 2008-02-19T15:41:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2008-02-19/gazprom-neft-boosts-oil-refining-by-7-3-in-2007-update1-.html

          
          
             OAO Gazprom Neft, the oil producer
owned by  Russia 's natural gas export monopoly, increased crude
oil refining by 7.3 percent last year to 26.15 million tons, or
an average 525,000 barrels a day.  
 The company's biggest refinery in Omsk raised output by 1.4
percent last year to 16.5 million tons, the St. Petersburg-based
oil producer said in a statement today.  
 Gazprom Neft's share of production from the Moscow oil
refinery rose 3.4 percent to 3.34 million tons of crude. Its
share of the Yaroslavnefteorgsintez refinery rose 33 percent to
6.3 million tons of oil. Total production of light refined
products rose 9 percent to 17.47 million tons, Gazprom Neft said.  
 Sales of oil products inside Russia rose 11 percent to 13.2
million tons. Oil-product exports were 11.6 million tons last
year, the company said, without giving a comparative figure.  
